Attendance Policy
1.	All members must attend the scheduled presentation.
2.	Any absence must be supported by appropriate documentation.
3.	Absence must be communicated to the instructor prior to the presentation date whenever possible.
4.	Members must attend scheduled team meetings regularly.
 
 Participation & Contribution
5.	All team members must contribute equally to the assignment/project.
6.	Tasks should be distributed fairly and documented.
7.	Any member who completes the assignment but does not attend the presentation (without valid reason) will have their marks capped at 40%.
8.	If a member neither attended the presentation nor contributed to the assignment, the member will receive a Fail grade.
9.	If peer evaluation indicates that a member did not meaningfully contribute to the assignment content and failed to attend the presentation, the member will receive a Fail grade.
10.	Any disputes regarding contribution must be discussed and documented before submission.
11.	The group reserves the right to report non-participation to the instructor if necessary.
12.	Inform the team in advance if unable to complete assigned tasks.
 
Academic Integrity
13.	All assignment work must be original.
14.	Plagiarism (copying from the internet, books, or other teams) is strictly prohibited.
15.	Proper references must be provided for any external resources used.
16.	AI tools may be used only if permitted by the instructor and must be properly acknowledged.
 
Professional Conduct
17.	Members must communicate respectfully.
18.	Members must meet agreed deadlines.
19.	Lack of communication will be considered non-participation.
20.	Respect each memberâ€™s ideas and suggestions.
 
Technical & Project Standards (For Software/Technical Assignments)
21.	Follow coding standards and naming conventions.
22.	Comment code properly.
23.	Test all modules before submission.
24.	Ensure the project is user-friendly and fully functional.
25.	Ensure the software runs without errors.
26.	Keep backup files (USB and cloud storage).
27.	Be prepared to answer technical questions during the presentation.

